			<ns0:name>kschi...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108470876877739532758/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Reopened. Found bug in fix. Part of the problem is that the data structures used, and the code, use the loaded segment memory to hold parsed bytes. As a result, buffering gets messy in that ALL users of the data must be aware of this and add protection code as appropriate.

Submitted CL that separates the parsed segment memory from the parsed bytes, so that down stream only needs to access the parsed bytes. If any buffering was needed to be added, it has already been done before they were added to the parsed bytes.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-12-20T22:31:32.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-12-20T22:31:32.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 7 by kschi...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=592#c7" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/592/comments/full/7" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>